
Overview of verb capitalize

The verb capitalize has 6 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                     
1. (3) capitalize, capitalise, take advantage -- (draw advantages from; "he is capitalizing on her mistake"; "she took advantage of his absence to meet her lover")
2. capitalize, capitalise -- (supply with capital, as of a business by using a combination of capital used by investors and debt capital provided by lenders)
3. capitalize, capitalise -- (write in capital letters)
4. capitalize, capitalise -- (compute the present value of a business or an income)
5. capitalize, capitalise -- (consider expenditures as capital assets rather than expenses)
6. capitalize, capitalise -- (convert (a company's reserve funds) into capital)
